    <h1>Biryani : My Best-Loved Dish</h1>
    <p>Biryani is a mixed dish popular in South Asia, made with <b>rice</b> and <b>meat</b> of the consumer's choice. To cater to vegetarians, the meat can be substituted with <b>vegetables</b> or <b>paneer</b>.</p>
    <h2>Origins of Biryani</h2>
    The origins of biryani can be traced back to ancient Persia <i>modern-day Iran</i>, where a similar dish called <q>pulao</q> or <q>pilaf</q> was prepared.<br>
    Another theory states that, biryani made it's way into India through the Mughal Empire, under the rule of King Babur.<br>
